WEBVTT

00:06.354 --> 00:06.571
.

00:06.615 --> 00:08.095
[tense music]

00:08.138 --> 00:09.270
- You an only child?

00:09.313 --> 00:11.315
- Yeah, I was.
- I am, too.

00:11.359 --> 00:13.796
Only children--scientifically,
more imaginative,

00:13.839 --> 00:16.059
especially those
with unreliable fathers.

00:16.103 --> 00:18.192
- Your dad--
is he the same Bill Hope

00:18.235 --> 00:20.194
that does the neighborhoods--
Willow Court and all that?

00:20.237 --> 00:21.717
- Yeah, that's him.

00:21.760 --> 00:23.849
After my dad took me
to the circus,

00:23.893 --> 00:25.677
I came up with Pretzel Jack.

00:25.721 --> 00:27.462
When my dad left,

00:27.505 --> 00:29.203
that's when he became real.

00:29.246 --> 00:31.727
It's him from back then.

00:31.770 --> 00:33.468
- You weren't the only kid
who had to invent

00:33.511 --> 00:35.426
a sidekick/guardian.

00:35.470 --> 00:38.212
- What was his name?
- Tall Boy.

00:38.255 --> 00:39.474
Everybody has

00:39.517 --> 00:41.780
their own emotional stuff,

00:41.824 --> 00:45.654
but for you and I,
that stuff can become real.

00:45.697 --> 00:47.395
- How do I kill him?

00:47.438 --> 00:49.397
- It is possible,
but here's the thing.

00:49.440 --> 00:51.703
You don't have to kill
Pretzel Jack

00:51.747 --> 00:53.575
You just learn
to control him.

00:53.618 --> 00:55.838
If you want to draw him out,
you have to get hurt.

00:55.881 --> 00:57.579
You have to get really hurt.

00:57.622 --> 01:01.583
You have to be willing
to go where it hurts.

01:01.626 --> 01:03.454
- There he is.

01:03.498 --> 01:05.891
- Jillian, stay calm.

01:05.935 --> 01:09.721
If you're calm,
he's calm.

01:09.765 --> 01:11.723
Focus.

01:11.767 --> 01:14.378
Deep breaths.

01:14.422 --> 01:18.469
♪

01:20.384 --> 01:23.344
[pencil scraping]

01:23.387 --> 01:26.347
[nostalgic music]

01:26.390 --> 01:33.441
♪

01:47.585 --> 01:50.632
[knock at door, door opens]

01:52.329 --> 01:54.505
- What are you still doing up?

01:54.549 --> 01:56.464
- I don't feel good.

01:56.507 --> 01:57.900
- What doesn't feel good?

01:57.943 --> 02:00.816
- I miss Dad.

02:00.859 --> 02:02.731
- Get in bed.

02:09.955 --> 02:12.610
- It's not even dark.

02:37.374 --> 02:38.810
[buzzing]

02:38.854 --> 02:41.813
[eerie music]

02:41.857 --> 02:48.907
♪

03:19.024 --> 03:22.898
[floor creaking]

03:22.941 --> 03:25.901
[suspenseful music]

03:25.944 --> 03:32.951
♪

04:36.841 --> 04:39.017
[gasps]

04:56.948 --> 04:59.516
[giggles]

05:00.604 --> 05:02.650
[giggles]

06:17.551 --> 06:19.422
- Let's go.

06:33.871 --> 06:35.917
[door closes]

06:44.969 --> 06:47.624
- You see what you did?

06:47.668 --> 06:49.191
[door creaks closed]

06:49.234 --> 06:51.585
- What?
- You tamed it.

06:51.628 --> 06:55.937
Your anger, your--
your stuff, all of it.

06:55.980 --> 06:57.765
It's yours.
It belongs to you.

06:57.808 --> 06:59.680
You can do whatever
you want with it.

06:59.723 --> 07:01.769
There's nobody else
like us who--

07:01.812 --> 07:04.902
who has what we have.

07:04.946 --> 07:07.731
- So what now?

07:07.775 --> 07:11.692
- Well, now you just stay calm.

07:11.735 --> 07:13.868
- But I can control him.

07:13.911 --> 07:15.783
I mean, if I wanted him
to come sit

07:15.826 --> 07:17.611
at the table with us,
I could do that?

07:17.654 --> 07:19.787
- Well, that would take
some training,

07:19.830 --> 07:21.136
but, yeah.

07:21.179 --> 07:22.616
- Training?

07:22.659 --> 07:24.574
Train him like a dog?

07:24.618 --> 07:28.665
- No, like I would have
to train you to develop--

07:28.709 --> 07:31.842
Like, how--
how do I put this?

07:31.886 --> 07:33.583
Like fine motor skills--

07:33.627 --> 07:35.846
to learn
to really control him,

07:35.890 --> 07:38.109
and then when you mastered
that, then, you know,

07:38.153 --> 07:42.505
it might be safe
to actually uncreate him.

07:42.549 --> 07:45.116
- Uncreate as in...

07:45.160 --> 07:47.031
kill?

07:48.990 --> 07:50.557
- Yeah.

07:51.819 --> 07:53.690
- How does that work?

07:53.734 --> 07:57.868
Does he just
keel over or disappear?

07:57.912 --> 08:00.001
- Let's just say you don't want
to be too close to him

08:00.044 --> 08:02.003
when it happens.

08:02.046 --> 08:06.529
[indistinct arguing]
- Why?

08:06.573 --> 08:09.010
- Would you just go?
- What the fuck?

08:09.053 --> 08:10.185
- Who is that?

08:10.228 --> 08:14.189
[indistinct arguing continues]

08:14.232 --> 08:16.974
Jillian.

08:17.018 --> 08:19.063
Jillian.

08:19.107 --> 08:22.719
Hey. Jill.

08:22.763 --> 08:23.894
Jill.

08:23.938 --> 08:25.896
Shit, he's awake.

08:25.940 --> 08:27.594
Shit!

08:27.637 --> 08:29.857
Shit!

08:29.900 --> 08:34.035
[pounding on door]

08:34.078 --> 08:36.211
Just--just stay calm.

08:36.254 --> 08:37.299
Deep breaths.

08:37.342 --> 08:40.128
You need to focus. Breathe.

08:40.171 --> 08:43.131
Yeah. Yeah, that's good.
- [breathing deeply]

08:45.960 --> 08:49.616
[glass shatters]
- Oh, shit.

08:49.659 --> 08:52.227
- Hello? 911?
- Sarah, we have to run!

08:52.270 --> 08:54.272
- [screams] Ow!

08:54.316 --> 08:56.884
[suspenseful music]

08:56.927 --> 08:58.712
- We got to go!

08:58.755 --> 09:01.062
♪

09:01.105 --> 09:04.674
- 911, what's your emergency?
Hello?

09:04.718 --> 09:07.721
♪

09:07.764 --> 09:09.723
- Tom!

09:09.766 --> 09:10.941
♪

09:10.985 --> 09:15.032
[indistinct radio chatter]

09:15.076 --> 09:17.121
Tom!

09:22.387 --> 09:24.694
[dog barking in the distance]

09:24.738 --> 09:27.741
[ominous, ambient music]

09:27.784 --> 09:34.835
♪

09:44.888 --> 09:47.935
[dog barking in the distance]

09:51.982 --> 09:54.115
- Oh, fuck. Fuck, fuck.
He's gonna fucking kill them.

09:54.158 --> 09:56.247
- Not if we get there first.

09:56.291 --> 09:57.988
- I tried to control him.
It didn't work.

09:58.032 --> 09:59.773
- You can learn
how to do this, okay?

09:59.816 --> 10:01.252
I'm gonna help you.

10:01.296 --> 10:02.950
And remember,
none of this is your fault.

10:02.993 --> 10:04.995
- Yes, it fucking actually is.
- No, it's not.

10:05.039 --> 10:06.823
Remember, focus.
Calm.

10:06.867 --> 10:08.695
Deep breaths. You can do this.
- Yeah.

10:08.738 --> 10:10.305
Why the hell did she come
to our house?

10:10.348 --> 10:11.741
- The woman?
Who is she?

10:11.785 --> 10:14.657
- Trust me, you don't--
- What?

10:14.701 --> 10:21.185
♪

10:23.405 --> 10:25.015
- This way.

10:30.542 --> 10:30.891
.

10:30.934 --> 10:33.023
- Why did a clown
come out of your basement

10:33.067 --> 10:34.459
and stab me in the fucking leg?

10:34.503 --> 10:36.331
- I can't explain it.
- Okay, well, try.

10:36.374 --> 10:39.203
- It's someone my wife knows.

10:40.727 --> 10:42.946
- Hello? Hello?

10:42.990 --> 10:45.470
[grunts]
Downstairs.

10:45.514 --> 10:48.473
[suspenseful music]

10:48.517 --> 10:50.475
♪

10:50.519 --> 10:52.347
- [breathing heavily]
Okay.

10:52.390 --> 10:54.828
- Someone your wife--
Someone your wife knows?

10:54.871 --> 10:56.264
That's not an explanation.

10:56.307 --> 10:57.744
- I don't have a good
explanation, okay?

10:57.787 --> 10:59.310
All you need to know
is that something

10:59.354 --> 11:01.008
is stalking us and we need
to get out of this situation.

11:01.051 --> 11:02.270
- Yeah, no shit.
- Okay.

11:02.313 --> 11:03.750
If you would have picked up
my calls,

11:03.793 --> 11:05.403
you would have known not
to just show up--

11:05.447 --> 11:07.144
- If I had picked up your
crazy, unwanted phone calls,

11:07.188 --> 11:08.842
then, yeah, I would have not
been stabbed by a clown.

11:08.885 --> 11:10.452
Thanks, Tom, I'll remember
that next time.

11:10.495 --> 11:12.106
- So it's crazy I want
to see my son?

11:12.149 --> 11:14.021
- He's not your son.
- Can we just stop?

11:14.064 --> 11:16.023
Appearances aren't gonna save
your marriage, okay?

11:16.066 --> 11:19.722
- That may be true,
but he's still not your son.

11:19.766 --> 11:21.724
Yes, okay,
I was unhappy in my marriage.

11:21.768 --> 11:23.726
I had an affair with you,
and I realized

11:23.770 --> 11:25.859
that I didn't want
to lose my marriage, okay?

11:25.902 --> 11:27.251
I'm sorry if I made you
believe otherwise.

11:27.295 --> 11:29.036
- Oh, no, this isn't about you.

11:29.079 --> 11:31.386
I'm not doing this
because I'm interested in you.

11:31.429 --> 11:34.955
I love my wife. I would never
cheat on her, all right?

11:34.998 --> 11:37.000
This is about me finding out
that you were pregnant

11:37.044 --> 11:39.176
and doing the math and then
you shutting me out, Sarah.

11:39.220 --> 11:40.874
- Yes, okay, I was scared
that if I found out

11:40.917 --> 11:43.050
my son was yours
that I would lose my family.

11:43.093 --> 11:45.226
So I kept a secret
to save my marriage.

11:45.269 --> 11:47.750
Does that sound familiar?

11:47.794 --> 11:49.143
But things
are different now, Tom.

11:49.186 --> 11:51.319
I'm happy. I love my husband.
I love my kids.

11:51.362 --> 11:54.061
That's why we're having
another baby.

11:54.104 --> 11:56.150
- Congratulations.

11:56.193 --> 11:58.413
- Listen, it's been eating me
alive as well,

11:58.456 --> 12:01.068
and that's why...
I got the test done,

12:01.111 --> 12:02.417
and I got the results back,

12:02.460 --> 12:04.811
and that's why I came
to your house today.

12:07.030 --> 12:08.945
- He's not my kid.

12:10.555 --> 12:13.515
[eerie music]

12:13.558 --> 12:20.783
♪

12:31.620 --> 12:34.797
[children shouting happily
in the distance]

12:41.586 --> 12:43.980
- Jill! Jill!

12:44.024 --> 12:47.549
Jill!
[doorbell ringing]

12:47.592 --> 12:50.900
[groans]

12:50.944 --> 12:53.163
[sighs]

12:57.646 --> 13:01.128
[line trilling]

13:01.171 --> 13:04.131
[ominous music]

13:04.174 --> 13:11.181
♪

13:38.034 --> 13:39.993
[object clangs]

13:40.036 --> 13:41.995
- Shit!

13:42.038 --> 13:49.045
♪

13:53.049 --> 13:56.487
- [breathing heavily]

13:58.011 --> 14:00.665
- Okay. Here.
Okay.

14:00.709 --> 14:02.537
[indistinct chatter]

14:02.580 --> 14:05.366
- [shuddering]

14:05.409 --> 14:08.499
- Okay.
Look...

14:08.543 --> 14:10.197
you're gonna wait here.
- No.

14:10.240 --> 14:11.894
- I'll bring back help.

14:11.938 --> 14:13.374
I promise.

14:16.986 --> 14:19.902
[tense music]

14:19.946 --> 14:26.909
♪

15:19.179 --> 15:22.138
[suspenseful music]

15:22.182 --> 15:25.272
♪

15:25.315 --> 15:28.623
[pounding on door]

15:28.666 --> 15:35.673
♪

16:02.091 --> 16:05.399
Shit! Shit!

16:05.442 --> 16:07.488
Come on!

16:16.758 --> 16:19.413
[door pounds open]
Ah!

16:19.456 --> 16:26.333
♪

16:26.376 --> 16:28.726
[screams]

16:33.166 --> 16:33.383
.

16:33.427 --> 16:34.558
- Tom!

16:36.604 --> 16:38.345
- Maybe he got out?

16:40.390 --> 16:42.218
- This way.

16:44.394 --> 16:47.789
[intense music]

16:47.832 --> 16:50.270
- [gasping]

16:52.228 --> 16:55.840
[shouting]

16:55.884 --> 17:00.715
♪

17:00.758 --> 17:02.847
[water splashing]

17:02.891 --> 17:04.327
- Oh, my God.

17:04.371 --> 17:06.199
No! Tom, no.

17:06.242 --> 17:08.549
- Jill, Jill, look, there's
nothing you can do down there

17:08.592 --> 17:11.378
that you can't do up here,
and you got to do it right now.

17:11.421 --> 17:17.427
♪

17:19.212 --> 17:21.431
- Jill, Jill, look at me.
Look at me. Look at me!

17:21.475 --> 17:23.346
I'm gonna help you,
all right?

17:23.390 --> 17:25.087
I know how to help you,
and I can do it,

17:25.131 --> 17:27.307
but you got to do everything
I tell you to--you understand?

17:27.350 --> 17:29.091
Do exactly as I say.

17:29.135 --> 17:30.745
Look at me,
right in my eyes.

17:30.788 --> 17:32.442
Connect with me.

17:32.486 --> 17:35.489
Concentrate only on what
I'm saying to you...

17:35.532 --> 17:38.318
and do not look away

17:41.147 --> 17:48.197
♪

17:51.635 --> 17:54.334
You created him, right?

17:54.377 --> 17:57.424
With your own pain
and your own fear.

17:57.467 --> 17:59.426
Those feelings are in you,

17:59.469 --> 18:02.429
all through your body,
running through you like blood.

18:02.472 --> 18:05.519
Now imagine that you can send
those feelings

18:05.562 --> 18:07.303
anywhere you want to
in your body.

18:07.347 --> 18:09.349
You can send them
to the top of your head

18:09.392 --> 18:10.915
or down to your belly button,
anywhere else.

18:10.959 --> 18:14.876
I want you to focus all your
energy on sending them down

18:14.919 --> 18:17.531
to the palms of your hands.

18:17.574 --> 18:19.794
Do that...now.

18:19.837 --> 18:26.409
♪

18:27.802 --> 18:29.847
- [gasps]

18:31.980 --> 18:33.634
- Everything you used
to create him,

18:33.677 --> 18:35.636
send it all to the palms
of your hands.

18:35.679 --> 18:37.420
Are you doing it?

18:37.464 --> 18:38.639
Good. Good.

18:38.682 --> 18:40.249
- [groans]
What's happening?

18:40.293 --> 18:42.164
- It's okay.
Don't worry. Don't worry.

18:42.208 --> 18:44.471
I'm gonna help you, okay?
It's all right.

18:44.514 --> 18:46.821
Send it all to the palms
of your hands.

18:46.864 --> 18:48.475
You're sending him there.

18:48.518 --> 18:50.607
You're sending him down
to the palms of your hands.

18:50.651 --> 18:53.871
So you're holding him
in your hands, yeah?

18:53.915 --> 18:55.786
Yeah, that's good.
More, more.

18:55.830 --> 18:58.180
Closer, closer, closer.

18:58.224 --> 18:59.834
Almost, almost.

18:59.877 --> 19:02.837
Yeah, yeah, there. There.

19:02.880 --> 19:05.535
♪

19:05.579 --> 19:07.929
Now focus on letting go.

19:07.972 --> 19:13.369
♪

19:13.413 --> 19:15.328
Now let go.

19:19.419 --> 19:22.465
- [gasping]

19:28.732 --> 19:31.692
[eerie music]

19:31.735 --> 19:35.261
♪

19:35.304 --> 19:36.566
Good.
You're almost there.

19:36.610 --> 19:38.873
I'm gonna help
get you there, okay?

19:38.916 --> 19:42.224
Now listen to me--I'm gonna say
the word "crush," all right?

19:42.268 --> 19:44.574
And when I say "crush,"
you're gonna clench your hands.

19:44.618 --> 19:46.315
You're gonna crush
what's in there,

19:46.359 --> 19:47.534
and you're gonna kill it,
all right?

19:47.577 --> 19:48.796
But something's gonna happen
to you.

19:48.839 --> 19:50.450
It's gonna hurt for a second.

19:50.493 --> 19:51.799
You're gonna feel like
you're the one being crushed,

19:51.842 --> 19:53.409
but you cannot stop--
you understand?

19:53.453 --> 19:55.759
Do not stop, all right?

19:55.803 --> 19:57.326
You ready?

19:57.370 --> 19:58.588
Okay, here we go.

19:58.632 --> 20:00.895
Three...

20:00.938 --> 20:03.376
two...

20:03.419 --> 20:05.508
one...

20:05.552 --> 20:07.641
crush.

20:07.684 --> 20:10.644
[eerie music]

20:10.687 --> 20:17.564
♪

21:14.621 --> 21:17.667
- [grunting]

21:22.498 --> 21:23.978
- Oh, my God.
- [coughing]

21:24.021 --> 21:26.067
- Oh, my God.
Are you okay?

21:28.112 --> 21:32.726
[Jillian gasps]
What just happened?

21:32.769 --> 21:34.684
- You did it.

21:34.728 --> 21:36.904
- [groans]

21:36.947 --> 21:39.036
No, I didn't.

21:39.080 --> 21:40.951
- Yeah, you did.

21:40.995 --> 21:43.040
I reached through you...

21:45.086 --> 21:48.524
We did it...
together.

21:51.048 --> 21:53.747
Doing it alone would have
killed you.

21:53.790 --> 22:00.841
♪

22:15.856 --> 22:17.945
- It's over.

22:27.824 --> 22:28.042
.

22:28.085 --> 22:29.957
- [sighs]

22:30.000 --> 22:31.959
[monitor beeping]

22:32.002 --> 22:35.049
- Thank you.

22:35.092 --> 22:38.879
[door opens]

22:42.230 --> 22:45.755
Oh, this...
gown is really annoying me.

22:45.799 --> 22:47.714
It's--it's like the tie
is all tangled.

22:47.757 --> 22:51.413
Can you just--do you mind
taking a look for me?

22:52.849 --> 22:54.547
- I can just get the nurse.

22:54.590 --> 22:56.853
- No, no, that'll take
three hours. Can you just...

22:56.897 --> 22:58.420
You guys,
can you just give us a minute?

22:58.464 --> 22:59.639
- Yeah, sure.

23:12.086 --> 23:13.783
- Yeah. No, the gown's fine.

23:16.525 --> 23:19.441
Do you even know who I am?

23:21.617 --> 23:24.751
- You're the woman my husband
has a kid with.

23:24.794 --> 23:27.797
- [scoffs]

23:30.147 --> 23:32.106
No.

23:32.149 --> 23:34.891
- What?

23:34.935 --> 23:37.981
[indistinct chatter]

23:46.773 --> 23:49.732
[dramatic music]

23:49.776 --> 23:56.826
♪

24:07.576 --> 24:08.882
[door opens]

24:08.925 --> 24:11.972
It's not Tom's?

24:13.103 --> 24:16.019
- No, he just wanted it to be.

24:19.762 --> 24:22.069
- He still thought it was,

24:22.112 --> 24:24.288
and he didn't tell me.

24:26.595 --> 24:29.163
So...

24:29.206 --> 24:33.689
Tom knows now
that it's not his?

24:38.955 --> 24:40.783
- You know, I don't know

24:40.827 --> 24:42.872
if this makes a difference
or not, but...

24:42.916 --> 24:45.962
he doesn't love me,
and he never did.

24:48.704 --> 24:51.838
- That doesn't matter.

24:51.881 --> 24:54.580
- What matters
is that he lied.

24:56.799 --> 24:59.672
- What matters
is that he lied.

24:59.715 --> 25:01.064
- We all lie sometimes.

25:01.108 --> 25:04.807
It doesn't mean
you don't love your partner.

25:04.851 --> 25:07.070
- I know Tom loves me.

25:08.681 --> 25:10.857
- I've been married
for 15 years--

25:10.900 --> 25:13.599
college boyfriend.

25:13.642 --> 25:16.079
Trust gets broken...

25:16.123 --> 25:19.300
but you can rebuild it.

25:19.343 --> 25:21.041
It's a belief.

25:21.084 --> 25:24.566
You can decide to have it
or--or not.

25:26.133 --> 25:28.788
- What if you can't?

25:28.831 --> 25:33.357
- But you can.
You're in control of you.

25:33.401 --> 25:38.232
You can decide to trust
or not to trust.

25:38.275 --> 25:41.365
- What if you can't?

25:42.802 --> 25:45.282
[indistinct chatter,
door opens]

25:45.326 --> 25:47.284
[sighs]

25:47.328 --> 25:49.112
- Hey.

25:51.201 --> 25:53.247
Hey, you okay?

25:59.296 --> 26:01.995
- Where's Tom?

26:02.038 --> 26:04.737
- I have no idea.
He just...

26:04.780 --> 26:06.956
I don't know.

26:10.307 --> 26:12.179
- I need to get out of here.

26:12.222 --> 26:13.963
Can you, um...

26:14.007 --> 26:15.922
can you give me a ride?

26:15.965 --> 26:18.185
[knock at door]

26:18.228 --> 26:20.274
- Yeah?

26:21.971 --> 26:23.756
- Hey.

26:23.799 --> 26:27.324
I, uh, brought you coffee.

26:27.368 --> 26:30.371
- Thanks.

26:30.414 --> 26:33.156
- Where's Jillian?
- She left.

26:34.941 --> 26:37.291
- [sighs]

26:37.334 --> 26:39.772
- Tom...

26:39.815 --> 26:42.426
my husband's on his way.

26:45.038 --> 26:47.649
- Right.

26:48.998 --> 26:51.348
- Good luck.

26:53.873 --> 26:55.831
- Thanks.

26:55.875 --> 26:57.964
- Pull over.

26:58.007 --> 27:00.923
[dramatic music]

27:00.967 --> 27:08.017
♪

27:21.727 --> 27:23.772
- You okay?

27:29.865 --> 27:32.041
- My inheritance.

27:32.085 --> 27:34.130
My father used
to build these neighborhoods

27:34.174 --> 27:36.176
all across the state.

27:36.219 --> 27:37.743
Homes...

27:37.786 --> 27:39.353
for families.

27:39.396 --> 27:43.792
- There aren't any families
there now.

27:43.836 --> 27:45.185
It's a...

27:45.228 --> 27:48.188
a ghost neighborhood.

27:48.231 --> 27:51.191
- I want you to show me
how to control it.

27:52.845 --> 27:54.411
- You sure?

27:55.848 --> 27:58.764
It's not easy.

27:58.807 --> 28:01.375
- I'll do what it takes.

28:01.418 --> 28:05.031
♪

28:05.074 --> 28:06.423
- Yeah.

28:08.077 --> 28:09.775
Okay.

28:16.869 --> 28:19.872
- I just, um...

28:19.915 --> 28:24.050
I can't go home right now.

28:24.093 --> 28:26.269
- I know the perfect place.

28:30.317 --> 28:30.534
.

28:30.578 --> 28:33.494
[telephone ringing,
indistinct chatter]

28:43.156 --> 28:45.245
- Where you going, Tom?

28:54.210 --> 28:56.560
[vehicle approaching]

29:03.872 --> 29:06.832
[dog barking in the distance]

29:06.875 --> 29:09.573
[car door opens, closes]

29:11.488 --> 29:14.796
- This is yours?
- It's my family's.

29:14.840 --> 29:17.364
I used to come here
during the summer.

29:17.407 --> 29:19.235
Doesn't get much use now,

29:19.279 --> 29:22.499
but I never had the heart
to sell it, so...

29:22.543 --> 29:25.807
- [groans]
- Are you okay?

29:25.851 --> 29:28.070
- Just, uh...

29:28.114 --> 29:30.116
a bit dizzy.

29:30.159 --> 29:31.944
- It's been a long day.

29:31.987 --> 29:33.902
It's catching up to you.

29:33.946 --> 29:36.992
Let's--let's go inside
and get some rest.

29:40.996 --> 29:43.956
- [vomiting]
- Oh, hey, hey.

29:43.999 --> 29:45.218
- [coughing]

29:45.261 --> 29:47.176
- Hey, you're okay.
You're okay.

29:47.220 --> 29:49.091
It's all right.

29:49.135 --> 29:50.963
Hey, this is normal.

29:51.006 --> 29:53.835
You're gonna be fine.

29:53.879 --> 29:55.489
All right?

29:55.532 --> 29:58.144
- [spits]
- Okay?

29:58.187 --> 30:01.103
- Yeah.
- Here we go.

30:01.147 --> 30:03.497
Let's go inside
and get some water, yeah?

30:03.540 --> 30:05.151
- Yeah.

30:06.500 --> 30:09.938
- I haven't been here
in forever.

30:09.982 --> 30:12.854
- This place
seems so familiar.

30:15.422 --> 30:18.599
- What happened at the pool?
- I told you--I don't know.

30:18.642 --> 30:20.122
- So you don't know
who this guy is

30:20.166 --> 30:22.037
that attacked you
and Sarah Winters?

30:22.081 --> 30:23.909
- No. No more than what I said.

30:23.952 --> 30:26.302
- Where's your wife?
- I don't know.

30:26.346 --> 30:28.217
- Are you protecting
Jillian, Tom?

30:28.261 --> 30:30.611
- What are you talking about?
- Hey, Tom...

30:30.654 --> 30:32.439
do you think
that your wife is capable

30:32.482 --> 30:34.441
of hiring someone to kill
for her?

30:34.484 --> 30:37.226
- Is there any reason that
your wife might want you dead?

30:37.270 --> 30:40.012
- [sighs]

30:40.055 --> 30:43.624
[insects chirping outside]

30:45.931 --> 30:49.195
[door closes,
footsteps approaching]

30:56.463 --> 30:59.509
- [sighs]

31:13.567 --> 31:17.223
I can't remember the last
time I threw up.

31:17.266 --> 31:19.573
- What you did today...

31:19.616 --> 31:21.618
it depletes you.

31:22.750 --> 31:24.230
You need to recover.

31:24.273 --> 31:26.928
- It's not just that.

31:26.972 --> 31:28.712
- What is it, then?

31:28.756 --> 31:31.715
- I don't know--it's like
a part of me is just gone,

31:31.759 --> 31:34.980
and there's nothing left
to keep me up straight.

31:37.243 --> 31:39.114
Is that crazy?

31:39.158 --> 31:40.724
- Of course not.

31:41.769 --> 31:45.251
You killed a part
of yourself today.

31:45.294 --> 31:47.644
Once you learn
to control these things,

31:47.688 --> 31:50.299
it'll be easier to let them
come and go.

31:55.087 --> 31:57.263
But now you need to sleep.

32:00.527 --> 32:04.096
Let's try and get as much rest
tonight as we can.

32:04.139 --> 32:06.446
You're gonna need it
for tomorrow.

32:08.317 --> 32:10.363
- [groans]

32:13.409 --> 32:15.455
Mm.

32:17.196 --> 32:20.286
Thanks.
- Of course.

32:20.329 --> 32:21.983
Here, uh...

32:22.027 --> 32:24.072
here you go.

32:26.379 --> 32:27.597
That should be fine.

32:27.641 --> 32:30.165
- That's great.
Thank you.

32:30.209 --> 32:31.993
- Um...

32:32.037 --> 32:33.516
have a good night.

32:33.560 --> 32:35.605
- Thanks. You too.

32:42.177 --> 32:45.137
[dramatic music]

32:45.180 --> 32:52.231
♪

32:53.362 --> 32:57.062
[cell phone vibrating]

33:20.563 --> 33:23.784
[cell phone vibrating,
door closes]

33:23.827 --> 33:26.047
- Jill?

33:36.362 --> 33:39.104
- Tom, this is Bill Hope,
Jillian's father.

33:39.147 --> 33:41.062
I've been trying to get
a hold of her,

33:41.106 --> 33:42.759
but she won't talk to me.

33:42.803 --> 33:44.761
I promise you I'm not trying
to pull anything here.

33:44.805 --> 33:47.764
I just have something
very important to tell her

33:47.808 --> 33:50.376
about--about her family.

33:50.419 --> 33:51.768
Can you please let her know

33:51.812 --> 33:53.553
that her dad needs
to talk to her?

33:53.596 --> 33:55.772
I'd like to tell her in person
if possible.

33:55.816 --> 33:58.732
I'm staying at
the Mill Road Inn, room 105.

33:58.775 --> 34:01.256
I can--I can come by tonight
or tomorrow,

34:01.300 --> 34:03.563
or she can come by here
if that's better.

34:03.606 --> 34:07.262
Please, I need to talk
to my daughter.

34:07.306 --> 34:10.874
♪

34:15.270 --> 34:18.447
[woman speaking indistinctly
on TV]

34:18.491 --> 34:21.102
[animals squeaking on TV]

34:21.146 --> 34:24.366
♪

34:24.410 --> 34:26.673
[knock at door]

34:35.160 --> 34:37.423
- Not the kid
you were expecting...

34:37.466 --> 34:39.425
Dad?

34:39.468 --> 34:42.123
♪

34:45.561 --> 34:45.779
.

34:45.822 --> 34:48.260
- Jill, pick up.
Come on.

34:48.303 --> 34:51.263
[suspenseful music]

34:51.306 --> 34:52.612
[engine turning over]

34:52.655 --> 34:54.614
[cell phone vibrating]

34:54.657 --> 34:56.659
- You left her alone.

34:56.703 --> 34:59.314
Doesn't mean I have to.

34:59.358 --> 35:01.882
I'm not gonna fail her
like you failed her.

35:01.925 --> 35:04.624
- Ian...

35:04.667 --> 35:08.584
for once in your life,
do what's right.

35:08.628 --> 35:11.283
- You know, when
I first moved in with you,

35:11.326 --> 35:13.720
I really looked up to you.

35:13.763 --> 35:16.549
It took me way too long
to realize

35:16.592 --> 35:18.812
how you were always trying
to cut me off at the knees.

35:18.855 --> 35:20.770
- Cut you off?

35:20.814 --> 35:22.555
I protected you.

35:22.598 --> 35:24.687
Did I say anything

35:24.731 --> 35:27.951
when the dog disappeared...

35:27.995 --> 35:32.782
or when that--that bully
from school went missing?

35:32.826 --> 35:36.438
- Well, you're nothing
if not a good liar.

35:36.482 --> 35:40.399
- Leave your sister alone.

35:40.442 --> 35:42.227
- Half-sister.

35:42.270 --> 35:44.664
Made you happy
to keep her from me, didn't it?

35:44.707 --> 35:46.709
- I am glad I did.

35:49.451 --> 35:51.192
You...

35:51.236 --> 35:53.716
have always been...

35:53.760 --> 35:56.371
a bad seed.

35:56.415 --> 35:59.331
[dramatic music]

35:59.374 --> 36:01.202
♪

36:01.246 --> 36:03.552
- [shuddering]

36:03.596 --> 36:06.947
[inhales deeply, shudders]

36:06.990 --> 36:08.514
[breathing rapidly]

36:08.557 --> 36:10.603
- Hey! Open your eyes!

36:10.646 --> 36:12.996
- [groaning]

36:13.040 --> 36:19.829
♪

36:21.831 --> 36:24.573
- [groaning]

36:24.617 --> 36:31.580
♪

36:31.624 --> 36:33.713
- [echoing]
Ian!

36:33.756 --> 36:35.845
Open your eyes!

36:35.889 --> 36:37.760
Ian!

36:43.026 --> 36:45.594
- As much as I hate
to admit it,

36:45.638 --> 36:48.380
it's got to come
from you, right?

36:48.423 --> 36:51.252
If she has it, too.

36:51.296 --> 36:53.298
- Ah, what?

36:56.388 --> 36:59.391
- It's your seed, asshole.

36:59.434 --> 37:02.394
[suspenseful music]

37:02.437 --> 37:05.614
♪

37:05.658 --> 37:08.487
- [screaming]

37:08.530 --> 37:15.581
♪

37:22.109 --> 37:25.286
- We have some cleaning up
to do.

37:34.469 --> 37:41.476
♪

37:48.004 --> 37:50.964
[mysterious music]

37:51.007 --> 37:58.014
♪

38:05.979 --> 38:09.983
[car door opens, closes,
engine turning over]

38:10.026 --> 38:16.903
♪

38:34.050 --> 38:36.488
- Bill, it's Tom.
You there?

38:38.403 --> 38:39.882
Bill!

38:39.926 --> 38:46.976
♪

38:50.632 --> 38:52.373
Bill?

38:52.417 --> 38:55.376
[tense music]

38:55.420 --> 39:02.427
♪

39:22.229 --> 39:25.406
[indistinct chatter]

39:27.756 --> 39:30.716
[eerie electronic music]

39:30.759 --> 39:37.766
♪

40:45.007 --> 40:49.490
♪

40:59.848 --> 41:03.504
- [groans softly]

41:03.548 --> 41:04.984
[knock at door]

41:05.027 --> 41:06.638
- Hey.
- Hey.

41:06.681 --> 41:08.161
- Morning.
- Morning.

41:08.204 --> 41:10.990
- You, uh--
you feeling any better?

41:11.033 --> 41:12.557
- Yeah.

41:12.600 --> 41:14.515
- Here.

41:14.559 --> 41:15.908
- Thanks. What's this?

41:15.951 --> 41:18.171
- This is herbal tea.

41:18.214 --> 41:21.261
It has turmeric
and cinnamon

41:21.304 --> 41:25.831
and lemon balm
and red raspberry leaves...

41:25.874 --> 41:27.659
and ginger.

41:27.702 --> 41:30.096
[both laugh]

41:30.139 --> 41:32.315
- That's--that's
a lot of ingredients.

41:32.359 --> 41:34.535
- Yeah, well,
it's real good for you.

41:34.579 --> 41:36.624
You're gonna need every little
bit of strength

41:36.668 --> 41:38.060
for your training.

41:41.673 --> 41:43.283
- Thank you.

41:43.326 --> 41:45.546
I really appreciate it.

41:45.590 --> 41:47.330
- Yeah, of course.

42:03.259 --> 42:05.305
How is it?

42:05.348 --> 42:08.830
- It's good.
- Good.

42:09.918 --> 42:12.138
I made it just for you.

42:13.400 --> 42:16.925
- ♪ Every time
you leave me, baby ♪

42:16.969 --> 42:19.841
♪ I said every time you go

42:19.885 --> 42:23.018
♪ I wonder if you're coming
back to see me ♪

42:23.062 --> 42:26.369
♪ I wonder where you go,
yeah ♪

42:26.413 --> 42:29.329
♪ Maybe it's my mind
that deceives me ♪

42:29.372 --> 42:31.592
[static whirring]
